      "role": "user",
      "content": "Thanks for that. I'm trying to weigh if these concerns are actually valid or if they're just being used as excuses to block progress. Looking at the actual long-term data, do these arguments about \"neighborhood character\" and \"infrastructure strain\" actually hold up, or are they mostly just NIMBY rhetoric used to prevent necessary urban evolution?",
