      "content": "The concerns about \"neighborhood character\" and \"infrastructure strain\" are often overstated by NIMBYs. In reality, high-density zoning can enhance neighborhood character by introducing diverse housing options and fostering a sense of community. As for infrastructure, cities that have implemented high-density zoning have often seen improvements in public transportation and utilities, offsetting the initial strain. These concerns are typically used by those resistant to change to maintain the status quo, rather than genuine worries about urban evolution.",
